# Visual Design Rules — CalvyBots Launchpad (v4 direction)

## Colour palette — cyan/dark

These are the canonical tokens. Use them via Tailwind config extensions or CSS custom properties in `css/style.css`.

| Token | Value | Use |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `bg` | `#1c1c1c` | Page background |
| `surface` | `#242424` | Widget cards, major surfaces |
| `elevated` | `#2e2e2e` | Raised controls, pills, dropdowns |
| `border` | `#3d3d3d` | Separators, card edges |
| **`accent`** | **`#2dd4bf`** | **Cyan — interactive highlight, focus, active states** |
| `text-1` | `#f0f0f0` | Primary text |
| `text-2` | `#9a9a9a` | Secondary/helper text |
| `text-3` | `#5c5c5c` | Muted metadata |
| `danger` | `#ff5c87` | Error, destructive action |
| `success` | `#33dd9c` | Confirmation, success state |

**No purple/violet in active UI states.** Any `.btn-*` rules in `css/style.css` that still use indigo or violet must be migrated to cyan variants when those selectors are touched.

## Depth model

- `body` uses ambient low-contrast gradient to avoid total flatness.
- Widget cards: layered gradient fill + soft edge tint + slight lift on hover.
- Hover state: border-lightening + `translateY(-1px)` lift at most.
- Avoid heavy box-shadows or bloom effects; prefer `rgba` accent tints.
- `backdrop-filter` and `blur` are acceptable sparingly for modal/overlay surfaces.

## Component rules

### Widget card (`.dash-widget`)
- Gradient fill from `surface` to `bg` direction.
- `border-radius: 0.75rem` (cards), `0.5rem` (controls).
- Hover: subtle border-color brighten + small lift.
- Resize handle visible only in edit mode, minimum 10×10px touch zone.

### Buttons
- Primary: cyan accent gradient, strong contrast text, `:focus-visible` cyan ring.
- Secondary/soft: dark neutral gradient + border, same focus ring.
- Destructive: `danger` colour only, never cyan.
- All buttons: minimum **42px** height on mobile.

### Inputs and textareas
- Dark background (`elevated`), high-contrast `:focus-visible` outline in `accent`.
- Placeholder text in `text-3` tone.
- No unstyled browser defaults; always include explicit focus styles.

### Widget title (`.widget-title`)
- `0.72rem`, `font-weight: 600`, `letter-spacing: 0.08em`, all-caps.
- Rendered **once** by the shell — never duplicated inside the widget renderer.

## Typography

- Page title (h1): `1.5–1.875rem`, weight 600, line-height 1.2.
- Body: `1rem`, weight 400, line-height 1.45.
- Caption/helper: `0.75rem`, muted text tone.
- Font stack: Outfit → Inter → system sans-serif. Load via Google Fonts CDN.

## Motion

- Max transition duration: **240ms**.
- Easing: `ease-out` only — no `ease-in`, no linear for UI transitions.
- Entry fade/slide for new widget cards: 150–220ms.
- Always add `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` block that disables non-essential animations.

## Accessibility

- `:focus-visible` required on every interactive element; `:focus` (without visible) should be styled identically or suppressed only for pointer users.
- Minimum touch target: **42×42px**.
- Icon-only controls: `aria-label` required.
- No duplicate widget titles in the DOM — shell renders title, widget body does not.
- Color contrast: primary text on surface must meet WCAG AA (4.5:1 for normal text).
- `aria-live="polite"` on the offline indicator strip.

## Mobile / standalone

- Single-column layout below `640px`.
- `env(safe-area-inset-*)` padding in standalone PWA mode.
- Sub-640px: disable widget body CSS resize to prevent scroll conflicts.
- Touch targets above fold must be reachable one-handed.
- Edit mode controls must remain accessible in portrait orientation.
